Jarvis RTOS — Build Targets

  [A] make (or make all)     Show this help
  [A] make build             Style check + debug ISO
  [A] make check-style       Validate kernel coding style (src/kernel/)
  [A] make check-config      Validate kernel configuration consistency
  [A] make config-summary    Print active configuration values
  [A] make debug             Build debug ISO
  [A] make release           Build production ISO
  [A] make clean             Remove all build artifacts
  [I] make run-debug-mode [<arch>]   Interactive debug shell (QEMU, mon:stdio)
  [I] make run-release-mode [<arch>] Interactive release shell (QEMU, mon:stdio)
         <arch> = x86|x86_64|arm|aarch64|riscv|riscv64  (default: x86_64)
  [A] make execute-test <arch> <build> <class>  Unified test runner
         <arch>  = x86|x86_64|arm|aarch64|riscv|riscv64
         <build> = debug|release
         <class> = none|selftest|all|<name>
           none     → interactive shell (no tests, mon:stdio)
           selftest → safe class, auto-shutdown (CI gate, 120s)
           all      → all classes, auto-shutdown (180s debug / 120s release)
           <name>   → specific test class, auto-shutdown (120s)
  [A] make debug-test <arch> <build> <class> <gdb-script>
         GDB batch surveillance. QEMU with -s -S, runs gdb-script,
         reports panic capture. 120s timeout.
  [A] make debug-shell <arch> <build> none <gdb-script> <shell-cmds>
         GDB + serial interaction. Reads commands from text file,
         sends them via serial after GDB continues.
  [A] make symbols           Kernel symbol table
  [A] make objdump           Kernel disassembly
  [A] make profiling         GCOV coverage capture
  [I] make rr-record         Record QEMU execution (deterministic replay)
  [I] make rr-replay         Replay recorded session with GDB stub (:1234)
  [I] make run-renode        Boot debug ISO in Renode (x86_64)
  [I] make run-renode RENODE_ARCH=aarch64  Boot AArch64 in Renode
  [I] make run-renode RENODE_ARCH=riscv64  Boot RISC-V 64 in Renode
  [A] make renode-test       Run selftest in Renode (x86_64)
  [A] make renode-test RENODE_ARCH=aarch64  Run selftest on AArch64
  [A] make renode-test RENODE_ARCH=riscv64  Run selftest on RISC-V 64

  [A] = autonomous (run and done, no interaction needed)
  [I] = interactive (user sits at the QEMU/GDB/Renode console)

  Examples:
    make run-debug-mode                       # interactive x86_64 debug QEMU
    make run-release-mode                     # interactive x86_64 release QEMU
    make run-release-mode arm                 # interactive AArch64 release QEMU
    make run-release-mode riscv               # interactive RISC-V 64 release QEMU
    make execute-test x86 debug none          # interactive QEMU (verbose)
    make execute-test x86 release all         # full release test suite
    make debug-test x86 debug all tools/gdb/test-batch.gdb  # GDB panic capture
    make debug-shell x86 debug none tools/gdb/init.gdb cmds.txt
